Introduction

Youngjae is a South Korean singer and actor under Forstar Company. He is a member of the boy group B.A.P.

On February 17, 2019, TS Entertainment stated that the four remaining members of B.A.P, after the departure of Bang Yong Guk in August 2018, and Zelo in December 2018, have all elected to not renew their contracts with the agency.

Following his departure from TS, he signed with J WORLD Entertainment and debuted as a solo artist on April 19 with the mini album "Fancy".

On August 29, 2019, Youngjae signed with Dmost Entertainment (later known as Starit Entertainment).

On March 14, 2022, Youngjae signed with Forstar Company as an actor.

On May 16, 2024, Youngjae took to social media to announce that he has left his current company, Forstar Company, and for fans to stay tuned for his future activities.
